B052C003V001	52	3	1	Therefore when we could no longer forbear, we thought it good to be left at Athens alone;
B052C003V002	52	3	2	And sent Timothy, our brother, and minister of God, and our fellowlabourer in the gospel of Christ, to establish you, and to comfort you concerning your faith:
B052C003V003	52	3	3	That no man should be moved by these afflictions: for yourselves know that we are appointed to this. 
B052C003V004	52	3	4	For verily, when we were with you, we told you before that we should suffer tribulation; even as it came to pass, and ye know.
B052C003V005	52	3	5	For this cause, when I could no longer forbear, I sent to know your faith, lest by some means the tempter may have tempted you, and our labour be in vain.
B052C003V006	52	3	6	But now when Timothy came from you to us, and brought us good tidings of your faith and charity, and that ye have good remembrance of us always, desiring greatly to see us, as we also 
B052C003V007	52	3	7	Therefore, brethren, by your faith we were comforted over you in all our affliction and distress:
B052C003V008	52	3	8	For now we live, if ye stand fast in the Lord.
B052C003V009	52	3	9	For what thanks can we render to God again for you, for all the joy with which we rejoice for your sakes before our God;
B052C003V010	52	3	10	Night and day praying exceedingly that we may see your face, and may perfect that which is lacking in your faith?
B052C003V011	52	3	11	Now God himself and our Father, and our Lord Jesus Christ, direct our way to you. 
B052C003V012	52	3	12	And the Lord make you to increase and abound in love one toward another, and toward all 
B052C003V013	52	3	13	To the end he may establish your hearts unblameable in holiness before God, even our Father, at the coming of our Lord Jesus Christ with all his saints. 
