B052C005V001	52	5	1	But of the times and the seasons, brethren, ye have no need that I write to you.
B052C005V002	52	5	2	For yourselves know perfectly that the day of the Lord so cometh as a thief in the night.
B052C005V003	52	5	3	For when they shall say, Peace and safety; then sudden destruction cometh upon them, as travail upon a woman with child; and they shall not escape.
B052C005V004	52	5	4	But ye, brethren, are not in darkness, that that day should overtake you as a thief.
B052C005V005	52	5	5	Ye are all children of light, and children of the day: we are not of the night, nor of darkness.
B052C005V006	52	5	6	Therefore let us not sleep, as 
B052C005V007	52	5	7	For they that sleep sleep in the night; and they that get drunk are drunk in the night.
