B062C002V003	62	2	3	And by this we do know that we know him, if we keep his commandments.
B062C002V004	62	2	4	He that saith, I know him, and keepeth not his commandments, is a liar, and the truth is not in him.
B062C002V005	62	2	5	But whoever keepeth his word, in him verily is the love of God perfected: by this we know that we are in him.
B062C002V006	62	2	6	He that saith he abideth in him ought himself also so to walk, even as he walked.
B062C002V007	62	2	7	Brethren, I write no new commandment to you, but an old commandment which ye had from the beginning. The old commandment is the word which ye have heard from the beginning.
